  <prompt>
    <goal>Trim BFF/API architecture docs to decisions-only</goal>
    <context>The BFF and API architecture documents contain implementation details that are better captured in code and .claude/patterns/. This task trims each file to retain only architectural decisions, constraints, integration boundaries, and rationale — removing implementation walkthroughs, endpoint listings that duplicate code, and step-by-step configuration guides.</context>
    <constraints>Preserve all decision/constraint content. Do not remove ADR references, integration boundary definitions, or security-related constraints. Only touch BFF/API-related docs listed in this task.</constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-procedure-refactoring-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-procedure-refactoring-r1/design.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    1. Read notes/architecture-audit.md for classification guidance on BFF/API docs.
    2. Read each target file fully:
       - docs/architecture/sdap-bff-api-patterns.md (trim)
       - docs/architecture/sdap-overview.md (trim)
       - docs/architecture/sdap-component-interactions.md (trim)
       - docs/architecture/sdap-document-processing-architecture.md (trim)
    3. For each file, identify and remove:
       - Implementation walkthroughs and code samples
       - Endpoint listings that duplicate what is in code
       - Step-by-step configuration or setup instructions
    4. Preserve:
       - Architectural decisions and rationale
       - Integration boundaries and data flow decisions
       - Security constraints and ADR references
       - Component responsibility definitions
    5. Record before/after line counts for each file.
  </steps>
  <tools>Read, Edit, Glob, Grep, Bash</tools>
  <outputs>
    - Trimmed: sdap-bff-api-patterns.md, sdap-overview.md, sdap-component-interactions.md, sdap-document-processing-architecture.md
